snippet.title: YABI - AJAVOLI ft. BLUESSS ( OFFICIAL AUDIO )
snippet.description:
Track 2 from the BOOMERANG mixtape, ‚ÄúAjavoli‚Äù featuring Bluesss, delivers smooth melodies and emotional storytelling. A song about love, reflection, and feelings that never fade, this track shows a softer but powerful side of Yabi The Goat.


Heartfelt thanks to RACHANA DAHAL  for the beautiful back vocals. Your voice added depth, emotion, and soul to this track. Truly grateful for your support and talent.

‚ÄòAjavoli‚Äô is inspired by the original song by Sudip Giri. The emotions, melody, and soul of the original track sparked a new creative direction, allowing this version to reflect personal experiences while honoring the essence and artistry of the original work. Much respect to Sudip Giri for the inspiration.‚Äù

snippet.title: Sajjan Raj Vaidya - Patra [Official Release]
snippet.description:
Letters within letters to let her know, that in all of my loving she is all I‚Äôve known. For when the night falls, and thoughts surround you and force a conversation, you realise neither time nor space can create distance from her of any kind. And so each day becomes a mere addition to how long you‚Äôve spent missing her. Each morning becomes a promise to face another night, once more, belonging to only her.
___________________________________________

About "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara"
"Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" is a popular Nepali folk song that originates from the Lamjung district of Nepal. It is a lively and upbeat song that is typically sung and danced to during festivals and social gatherings.

The lyrics of the song are in the Nepali language and describe the beauty of the Lamjung district's natural scenery, including the mountains, rivers, and forests. The song also celebrates the joy and happiness of the people living in Lamjung and their culture and traditions.

The musical arrangement of "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" typically features traditional Nepali instruments such as the madal (a type of drum), tungna (a stringed instrument), and sarangi (a bowed instrument). The song has a catchy melody and rhythm that are easy to dance along to.

Over time, "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" has become a beloved Nepali folk song that is popular across the country and is often performed by musicians and dancers at cultural events and festivals.

The lyrics of the song are in the Nepali language and describe the beauty of the Lamjung district's natural scenery, including the mountains, rivers, and forests. The song also celebrates the joy and happiness of the people living in Lamjung and their culture and traditions.

The musical arrangement of "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" typically features traditional Nepali instruments such as the madal (a type of drum), tungna (a stringed instrument), and sarangi (a bowed instrument). The song has a catchy melody and rhythm that are easy to dance along to.

Over time, "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" has become a beloved Nepali folk song that is popular across the country and is often performed by musicians and dancers at cultural events and festivals.

snippet.title: She & Him - I Thought I Saw Your Face Today (Official Lyric Video)
snippet.description:
The official lyric video for "I Thought I Saw Your Face Today" by She & Him

Subscribe To She & Him on YouTube: 
https://www.youtube.com/@SheandHimOfficial?sub_confirmation=1

Follow She & Him: 
http://www.sheandhim.com
http://www.instagram.com/sheandhim

http://www.twitter.com/sheandhim

Stream on Spotify:  https://bit.ly/ITISYFTSpotify
Stream on Apple Music: https://music.apple.com/us/song/i-thought-i-saw-your-face-today/1839131590
Stream on YouTube Music: https://bit.ly/ITISYFTYTMusic

Lyrics: 
I thought I saw your face today
But I just turned my head away
Your face against the trees
But I just see the memories
As they come, as they come

And I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall in love again

I saw it glitter as I grew
And loved it, boy, I never knew
I thought this place was heaven-sent
But now it's just a monument
In my mind, in my mind

And I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall in love again

The cars and freeways implore me to stay away, out of this place
My mother said, "Just keep your head, and play it as it lays"
The cars and freeways implore me to stay away, out of this place
My mother said, "Just keep your head, and play it as it lays"

I somehow see what's beautiful
In things that are ephemeral
I'm my only friend of mine
And love is just a piece of time
In the world, in the world

And I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall in love again
No, I couldn't help but fall...

#SheAndHim #IThoughtISawYourFaceToday

snippet.title: Darling Maeju - Preezol Nepali | Official music video | Unisha Sherpa Deshar | Jyasa Films
snippet.description:
This song tells the story of love at first sight, a powerful and unforgettable feeling that transcends culture. Though I'm not Newar, I wanted to express my personal experience through the beauty of Newari language and music. It‚Äôs a celebration of love, connection, and that magical moment when everything changes. Whether you're familiar with Newari culture or not, love is universal. This track is a tribute to the emotions we all share. I hope it resonates with anyone who has ever experienced that instant spark.

The Gayatri Mantra is a powerful and ancient chant from Hinduism. It is believed to bring peace, prosperity, and spiritual guidance for those who recite it. The mantra is a prayer to the divine light and wisdom that illuminates our path towards enlightenment. It is traditionally chanted before and after meditation, and is often used during yoga practices. The Gayatri Mantra is considered to be one of the most sacred of all mantras, and is said to have the power to protect and purify the mind, body, and soul.

snippet.title: Fuba Tamang - Kich Kich (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by Fuba Tamang performing Kich Kich ¬© 2026 Dami Entertainment.

Kich Kich is a fun, playful song filled with energy and good vibes üí´‚Äîmade to tease that special someone. Hit play and enjoy the vibe!

Written/ Composed and Performed by Fuba Tamang
Beat Prod/ Mix/Master - @BrijeshShrestha@NessStudio

Co-star: Doma Lama

Director: @yanjitamang8868 
DOP/ Cinematographer: Labesh Shrestha
Asst. Cinematographer/ Gaffer: Javed Khan
Edit/ Visuals: Gaurav Bista/ Jenish Maharjan 
MUA: Sushmita (Saiira)

Special Thanks

Anjali Gurung 
Choeden
Maddynast @maddynast
Prashant Shah @ridewithnepaus
Sabina (Aliendoescooking)
Adam (StudioKilla)

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-
Lyrics:

Chorus:
Nagara dherai kich kich,
Baby can you stop please,
Why you trippin‚Äô like this,
Baru deu na malai ek kiss, X 2

Verse:
Timro bani risauni, Sano kuramani,
Sadhai bhari ago timi hunchu ma chai pani,
Ah ah ayy,
Timi sadhai bhari ago,
Jailey timle jitnu parney kailey aaucha mero palo?
Haha
I‚Äôm kidding I ain‚Äôt waiting for my turn,
Jati kich kich maya badhdo raicha jhan,
Jhan jhan jiskauna lagney raicha maan,
Maan maan nadhukhau you‚Äôre my number one!

Aaba dherai nasatauna,
Aaudaina malai fakauna,
Neu khojna haina bhau khana haina matra aaucha maya launa,
Riss-rag sabai let go,
Maya prem ma huncha high-low,
Gucci-Louise V, bhana k chaiyo,
Timro kura sai ma sai (100/100) ho.

Pre-chorus:
Tara dherai ber risauda chai I don‚Äôt feel good,
Garo sarai garo baby bujhna timro mood,
Baby bujhna timro mood‚Ä¶.

Chorus:

Nagara dherai kich kich,
Baby can you stop please,
Why you trippin‚Äô like this,
Baru deu na malai ek kiss, X 2

Verse:
Thacha malai timro sabai aani bani,
Jati risayeni antyama timlai ma nai ho chainey,
Timro mood swing, tala mathi debrey dainey,
Chin-chin ma rotey ping jhai mero dimag nai ghumauney,

Uni arru bhanda different,
Uni miss independent,
Uni bhanchin timi mero kurai bujhdainau,
Paila jasto chainau aajkal change bhako chau,

I said- baby i‚Äôm grinding 24/7 for us,
Nasochnu dherai baby matra garnu malai trust,

Yeah, you gotta trust me baby,

Bhar para ma ma sankuchit bhawana narakhnu,
Dherai samaya lagdaina sanka le lanka jalaunu,
Guddi garnu choda baru chuni deu tyo oothle,
Halka maya satey huncha sabai kura okay!

Pre-chorus:
Tara dherai ber risauda chai I don‚Äôt feel good,
Garo sarai garo baby bujhna timro mood,
Baby bujhna timro mood‚Ä¶.

Chorus:

Nagara dherai kich kich,
Baby can you stop please,
Why you trippin‚Äô like this,
Baru deu na malai ek kiss, X 2

snippet.description:
seek refuge in the feet of Lord Hanuman, the remover of all sorrows, with the soulful bhajan "Hey Dukh Bhanjan Maruti Nandan," presented by Shree Dhun.
